reason.tex:


\begin{align}
	\text{If } z &= \ea\text{ then } dx = -\frac{dz}{4} \\
	\therefore I &= \int \sec^2 \ea\cdot dx \\
	&= -\frac{1}{4}\int \sec^2 z \cdot dz 
\end{align}



The standard result is \[\qquad \int \sec^2 z\cdot dz = \tan z + C\]

And therefore 
\begin{align}
	I &= -\frac{1}{4}\int \sec^2 z\cdot dz = -\frac{\tan z}{4} + C \\ 
	&= -\frac{\tan \ea}{4} + C 
\end{align}
